Obviously, not this monster let out a loud roar and tried to charge at Sasarin directly. Thank goodness, Sasarin, despite its massive body, was agile enough to avoid it in time. However, Nisi still couldn't help but scream and almost slipped off Sasarin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nicky exclaimed.
“Sight in on their heads!”
"It's too difficult!"
Sazalin let out a roar, circled once, and flew towards the mountain he called home.  The black monster followed close behind, but when it was attacked by flames from behind, it became disoriented.  This monster had not yet realized it had gained another opponent.  Sazalin slowed down, then struck the monster's head with his tail, sending it off course, and the monster was further panicked.
A monstrous creature let out a deafening roar and a shrill, rasping sound from its throat as it shot straight up into the air, spewing out something from its mouth. Suddenly, the surrounding area turned pitch black, as if the creature was sucking in the light from the sky and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sasarin's vision went black, trying to step back but found himself hitting the treetop and then falling onto the empty space. The monster seemed to know where Sasarin had fallen, heading straight for him and dragging the dark cloud along.
“Kayer!” Tenruk shouted as she flew out of the cloud, beginning to circle, trying to find Nyx and Sazalin in the darkness below. “What are we going to do? Kayer……? Kayer, where are you?”
Nixi struggled to her feet. She knew she had to be badly hurt, but her bizarre, unnatural healing powers were already kicking in. Sasarin's situation was different, he lay powerless on the ground, leaning against a tree he had crushed. Nixi made a determined effort to reach Sasarin, but everything in front of her was pitch black, and it was hard to see anything at all. There were terrifying shadows everywhere and something was screaming in the shadows.
A terrifying club-like tail came crashing down to the ground, sending Nicci flying. She noticed the tail flailing wildly but its target didn't seem to be her. Nicci strained to see what was happening, the beast roaring, its claws raking frantically at the darkness it was conjuring. Something was darting through the shadows, poised to strike at the beast.
Suddenly, a gunshot rang out through the air, and the monster fell silent, lying motionless on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Cayel stood on top of the monster's corpse, his rifle in hand, panting heavily.
"That was...this is one of the most bizarre shadow leaps I've ever done...Tantare Carthagon...” Kayel gasped, his voice barely above a whisper. For some reason, his eyes glinted with a dark light, and a dark energy swirled within him. But just as Kayel opened his mouth to speak, his organic armor recovered its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
A while later, Nicce finally understood what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed a mysterious shadow ability, but he rarely used it because most people thought it was evil and terrifying. However, Nicce didn't know that Kayel could use this ability in any darkness. And from Kayel's performance, he was also very surprised.
"Are you alright?" Nixi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, I'll be fine soon." Kayel gazed at his "masterpiece," and at that moment, Tenuk landed beside him, shifting back into its original shape of Sbast.
Now, the monster no longer moves, they can take a good look at it and see what it really is. Its skin was black and shiny, covered with a layer of gooey liquid, the mucus firmly attached to the monster's body. It had four wings and four legs, with long, thin claws on the end of each leg, and two straight horns on its skull.
Tenuk and Kael didn't even have time to ask what the hell it was, when a monster suddenly leaped out of the nearby bushes, screaming. Just then, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, which slid a distance before coming to a stop in front of Nisi. Nisi couldn't afford to hesitate, and grabbed his shotgun, pointing it directly at the monster's head and firing. The monster was instantly killed.
"Oh no...” Retrivic muttered, sitting in the driver's seat, and fumbled to turn off the engine before climbing down from the truck. "Uh, I didn't mean to. Are you all okay?"
"You've missed all the good shows!" Tu'er muttered to himself. "Where did you go?"
"It's you who left me behind. I've caught up as best I can... Please, what are these awful things?"
Retwick's problem was solved by Sasarin, who has been standing up. He was covered in cuts and scratches all over, and looked a bit dazed, but his injuries didn't seem too serious.
"You killed the corruptors! Those infected monstrosities. When corruption attacked your gods, these creatures were left behind."
"You're saying... we... helped kill the terrifying monster god?" Tenruk stuttered.
